By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Speaker of House of Representatives, Rt. Hon. Yakubu Dogara and Governor Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto state, have eulogised a former Member of the House of Representatives and a chieftain of the All Progressive Congress (APC), Hon. Robinson Uwak on his birthday. Hon. Uwak represented the people of Oron federal constituency of Akwa Ibom state in the 7th National Assembly and a close ally of both Dogara and the former Speaker, Tambuwal. In a congratulatory message personally signed on Tuesday, Speaker Dogara prayed the young former lawmaker for grace and God’s guidance. “Dear Hon. Robinson Uwak, as you add another year to your age today, the 4th of June, be rest assured that I celebrate with you. “It is my prayer that you age gracefully, with wisdom and God’s guidance. Congratulations and best wishes”, Dogara said. Similarly, the Sokoto Governor, while congratulating Hon. Uwak on his birthday, described him as “one of the prodigy of the 7th House of Representatives”, which he (Tambuwal) presided. “Dear Hon. Robinson Uwak, I congratulate you on the auspicious occasion of your birthday. “You are fondly remembered as one of the prodigy of the 7th House of Representatives. “It is my prayer that you continue to soar high in all your endeavors. Happy Birthday and many happy returns”, Tambuwal wrote. Hon. Uwak, who represented Oron federal constituency at House of Representatives between 2011 to 2015, was also a Director of Youth Mobilisation in President Muhammad Buhari campaign organization and one of the nucleus in the Hon. Umar Bago speakership campaign organization.